---
import Default from '../../layouts/Default.astro';
---
<Default title="Autonomous Research Lab · Harshith Kantamneni" description="Autonomous research operations lab." current="labs">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-parallax-layer hero-parallax-layer-1" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-parallax-layer hero-parallax-layer-2" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="container">
      <span class="index-number">Lab module · live</span>
      <h1 style="max-width: 16ch;">Autonomous Research Lab</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        An autonomous research operations lab. A Director and specialist agents
        running on commodity hardware, governed by pre-registration discipline, a
        tiered persistent memory, reproducibility gates, and honest negative results.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-meta">
        <span><strong>Status</strong> Live</span>
        <span><strong>Active since</strong> 2026</span>
        <span><strong>Type</strong> Research operations</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="padding-top: 0;">
    <div class="grid-editorial">

      <article class="body">
        <h2>What this lab is</h2>
        <p>
          A research operations lab focused on small-model experimentation under
          constrained local compute. The lab plans experiments, pre-registers
          hypotheses and falsifiers, runs them on local hardware, evaluates results,
          archives artifacts, and decides what to do next.
        </p>
        <p>
          It runs in a tmux loop on a single MacBook. One cycle per Claude session.
          State persists across cycles via a three-tier markdown memory.
        </p>

        <h2>Operating model</h2>
        <ul style="padding-left: var(--space-5); line-height: var(--lh-body);">
          <li><strong>Director.</strong> Picks experiments each cycle, dispatches specialists, owns cycle outcome</li>
          <li><strong>Specialists.</strong> Scientific reasoning, methodology, code review, reproducibility, and adversarial review</li>
          <li><strong>Knowledge Manager.</strong> Closeout discipline at every cycle close</li>
          <li><strong>Evaluator.</strong> Independent verdict on cycle PASS, PARTIAL, or FAIL (binding)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Verification discipline</h2>
        <p>Three structural principles, shared across the lab framework:</p>
        <ol style="padding-left: var(--space-5); line-height: var(--lh-body);">
          <li><strong>External verdict.</strong> At least one verdict per cycle from a system the lab cannot edit</li>
          <li><strong>Pre-registered falsifier.</strong> Every claim declares, at open, a concrete observation that would invalidate it (immutable)</li>
          <li><strong>Adversarial payoff.</strong> At least one actor whose payoff increases when others' claims are falsified</li>
        </ol>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-7); color: var(--text-secondary);">
          For the current cycle, recent dispatches, and what is shipping this week,
          see <a href="/now">Now</a>. Reports from this lab are forthcoming.
        </p>
      </article>

      <aside class="marginalia">
        <p><strong>Lab type</strong></p>
        <p>Research operations</p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>Active since</strong></p>
        <p>2026</p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>Hardware</strong></p>
        <p>Single MacBook (M3 Pro, 18 GB)</p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>Focus</strong></p>
        <p>Small-model experimentation under constrained local compute</p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>Memory</strong></p>
        <p>Three-tier markdown (hot, wiki, log)</p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>Discipline</strong></p>
        <p>Pre-registration, reproducibility gates, honest negative results</p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>Framework</strong></p>
        <p><a href="https://github.com/Drogon4231/autonomous-lab-systems">autonomous-lab-systems</a></p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>Live status</strong></p>
        <p><a href="/now">/now</a></p>
      </aside>

    </div>
  </section>

</Default>
